(fifthQuint)Phase 0 Analysis of Ixazomib (MLN9708) in Patients With Glioblastoma.

 PRIMARY OBJECTIVES: I.

 Measurement of tissue concentration of ixazomib (ixazomib citrate) in a glioblastoma after preoperative administration.

 II.

 Measurement of blood and plasma concentration of ixazomib during surgical sampling after preoperative administration.

 SECONDARY OBJECTIVES: I.

 Assessment of the safety of ixazomib after single dose administration in glioblastoma patients undergoing surgery for tissue concentration assessment.

 OUTLINE: Patients receive ixazomib orally (PO) 3 hours before surgery.

 After completion of study, patients are followed up for 30 days and then periodically thereafter.

